Summary: Not a helicopter, blimp, or other known slow moving aircraft.
divs: sighting detailsi was a utility worker on a call in felda, florida. i was leaving palm and pines mobile home park traveling south on sr 29 when i noticed a slow but big pulsating light over gopher ridge orange grove to the east. the shadow cast by the light showed the underside of a square, box like structure moving very slowly from south to north. my view was quick, but as i thought about it on the way home, i knew there are no known man made objects that travel or resemble what i'd just saw. the light was bowl shaped, white and pulsed at a rate too slow for aircraft id lights. the altitude of the vehicle never varied and the flight path was straight and due south\north. i can't estimate the size of the craft, but it was certainly bigger and slower (and stranger) than anything man can build.
